title: PhysicsForm
description:
-CONTROLS-
Click the buttons to interact.
  - Button Number 1 is the 'Add Clone' button.
  - Button Number 2 is the 'Switch Costume' button.
  - Button Number 3 is the 'Record' button (you can tell if you're recording actions if there's a red dot next to the play/pause button)
  - Button Number 4 is the 'Create Action' button. (Press SPACE to add a new action)
  - Button Number 5 is the 'Play/Pause' button. (It pauses gravity, not animation!)
Click and Hold the shape in the centre of your canvas to move it around.

-NOTES-
This 'game' is better on full screen. Just be aware of that when you're playing.
There is a one second delay to the record button so you have time to get set up. Note that for when you're making a movie!
You have to triple click the record button when you're done recording. It's a bug, but I might leave it in the next version...

title: PicoChat
description:
PicoChat - a safe way to communicate.
Because you have free speech and can say some nasty stuff on the Scratch comment system, I've created a platform where you can message safely. Just click the maximise button, click it again, and you can message off a whitelist!
(New Scratchers can't use this due to the use of cloud variables)
Click 1 to switch to Pico mode.
Click 2 to switch to Tera mode.
Happy messaging!

Also, be careful of what you say- everyone online (on PicoChat) can see The Spread, so if you do catch someone being unkind on The Spread, let me know on my accounts,
@Gifboythegamer10 and @trashcanrobber6.

Originally shared August 3rd, 2025.

List# 1.0.0
description:
Hello and welcome to the List# community!
There are five commands you can run in this new-fangled programming language:

'add' - Adds two digits together.
'sub' - Subtracts two digits apart.
'print-' - Prints a custom response.
'stamp-' - Stamps a shape (e.g. circle)
'[]' - Waits for .1 second(s)

[] is used as an example as to how List# runs. It is intended as a placeholder command.

Comment 'List# support' to become a part of the List# community!

By @Gifboythegamer10. (Original Project)

title: -check.io-
description:
---------------------------------------------------------------------
1.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------
-INFO AND DESCRIPTION-
This is currently some broad strokes of the full game, but I assure you this is going to be GREAT! 
And plus, the versions will be stored IN-GAME, instead of separate projects, so this is actually quite a revolutionary project!!!
-CONTROLS-
Arrow Keys to move.
-BASICS-
If you are red, you are the SEEKER. Your job is to find the HIDER after the timer runs out, and there is no time limit.
If you are blue, you are the HIDER. Your job is to hide somewhere on the map. You can go anywhere at any time, but try not to let the SEEKER see you!
The other players are just well-coded bots. It's unlikely they'll find you because their movements are dependent on so many variables with random outputs.
-WAYS TO WIN-
There is currently no way to win the game at the minute.
-POWERUPS-
There are currently no powerups.
-WARNINGS AND NOTES-
This doesn't fully work yet. I just need to keep on working at it.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
[Room for other updates]
---------------------------------------------------------------------
CHANGELOG AND MILESTONES
-Date- -Thing-
04/01/2025 - Initial Release, 1.0. Broad Strokes.
